          "text": "Math learning",
          "startTime": "22:30",
          "duration": "1h",
          "plannedIds": [],
          "notes": "**Martingales**: a mathematical model of a \"fair game.\" A sequence of random variables $X_1, X_2, \\dots, X_n$ is a martingale if the expected value of the next observation, given all the past observations, is exactly equal to the most recent observation:$E[X_{n+1} | X_1, X_2, \\dots, X_n] = X_n$ï¼Œوƒ³è±،ه¤ڑè½®وٹ›ç،¬ه¸پèµŒé’±ه°±وک¯ن؛†\n\n**Optional Stopping Theorem (OST)**: If $M_n$ is a martingale and $\\tau$ is a valid stopping time (a rule for stopping that only depends on the present and past, not the future), then under certain bounded conditions:$$E[M_\\tau] = E[M_0]$$\n\nè؟™é‡Œstopping timeن¸چوک¯constant. ن¸¾ن¾‹ï¼Œه¦‚و‍œوˆ‘وœ‰100ه‌—ï¼Œهپœو­¢و‌،ن»¶وک¯èµ¢هˆ°150وˆ–è€…è¾“ه…‰ï¼Œè؟™ن¸¤ç§چç»“ه±€çڑ„وœںوœ›ن»چç„¶وک¯100ï¼Œو‰€ن»¥وک¯p * 150 + (1 - p) * 0 = 100\n\nè؟کçœ‹ن؛†ن¸‹و°´هچ°çڑ„ه®‍çژ°و–¹و³• (a hash value depending on the previous context)",
          "createdAt": "2026-03-04T07:34:36.414Z"
        }
